# UI and Styling Framework

This application uses Bootstrap 5 as its primary CSS framework with additional libraries for enhanced UI elements.

## CSS Framework and Libraries
- **Bootstrap 5**: Core CSS framework for responsive layout and components
- **Font Awesome 6**: Icon library
- **Google Fonts**: Typography with Poppins as primary font
- **Glide.js**: For carousels and sliders
- **Fancybox**: For image lightboxes and galleries

## UI Component Patterns

### Cards
Used for containing related content with consistent styling:

```html
<div class="card">
    <div class="card-body">
        <!-- Card content -->
    </div>
</div>
```

### Form Groups
Consistent form element styling:

```html
<div class="form-group">
    <label for="inputId">Label Text</label>
    <input type="text" class="form-control" id="inputId" name="inputName">
    <small class="form-text text-muted">Help text</small>
</div>
```

### Alerts
For feedback messages:

```html
<div class="alert alert-success|danger|warning">
    <p>Alert message</p>
</div>
```

### Navigation
Bootstrap navbar with dropdown support:

```html
<nav class="navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-light">
    <!-- Navigation content -->
</nav>
```

## Responsive Design
- Mobile-first approach using Bootstrap's grid system
- Use of responsive utility classes for spacing and visibility
- Consistent breakpoints (xs, sm, md, lg, xl) across the application

